This ESTIMATOR position requires broad skills and solid expertise. 



The candidate should have the following: 



> Strong hands-on experience in all aspects of metal fabrication especially quoting; 

> Deep knowledge regarding the types of metals, finishes, and thickness;

> Uses both basic and advanced calculations to determine the current and potential productivity of a process; 

> Uses analytical skills to evaluate and interpret data; 

> Have skills in creating reports and describing the results to company decision-makers.





DUTIES and RESPONSIBILITIES



+ Create quotes for machine shop and sheet metal. The Estimator must be able to quote sheet metal fabrication jobs A-Z based on hands-on experience and review of drawings and all details required by customers; 

+ Use SolidWorks, Fusion360 or other engineering drawing software

+ Must understand sheet metal fabrication details, how to measure parts to thousandths and have deep knowledge of metal finishes and 3rd party metal treatments or metal powder coating; 

+ Use skills in project management and mathematics to better understand the current processes and procedures of the company, then work to improve them; 

+ Manage production schedules and coordinate services to maximize productivity; and 





QUALIFICATIONS



> Minimum of 3 years of experience, preferably in a metal fabrication environment; 

> Strong written and verbal communication skills; 

> Must be aware of a business’s needs while making technical recommendations understandable; 

> Good common sense and business sense; 

> Be able to handle stress and perform consistently in a fast-paced demanding environment; and 

> Ability to work with a team and exercise independent decision-making.
